  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just looked up the date and I see I made, I want to make a correction.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The German attack on Poland I stated was 1940 September the 1st.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is the wrong date.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The right date was September the 1st, 1939, not 1940.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in-- in all this turmoil, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it-- I-- I learned, I saw at that time that adversity affected people entirely different ways.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In one way, people that were not very religious before all of sudden, the adversity brought out of the-- brought out-- they became all of sudden very religious.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And those that were religious before, lived a religious life, it had the opposite effect on them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'll tell you why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is what reminded me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So people started to stop and to-- to pray on the field but by the field, the highway was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We weren't too far from the highway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "All of a sudden, we noticed German military, in military trucks, were going somewhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were going up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, all of a sudden, one guy that was a very religious guy, a [HEBREW], from a small community.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I knew the community but I didn't know the man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he started yelling and screaming, he says, do you-- do you want to-- to draw attention to yourself?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had the tallit on, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are Germans.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We kind of, even though the Hungarians did all that but we kind of were scared more of the Germans than we were scared of the-- and at that time, I remember that this man said, he said, I laid [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, very religious Jews would lay two different kinds of [HEBREW], not one.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know what [HEBREW] is.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
